Danity Kane is an American pop and R&B girl group signed to Bad Boy Records, first established in 2005. Formed on the second installment of MTV&#039;s Making the Band reality television series, the quintet is comprised of singers and songwriters Shannon Bex, Aundrea Fimbres, Aubrey O&#039;Day, Dawn Richard, and Wanita "D. Woods" Woodgette.

Their self-titled debut studio album was released in 2006 and achieved success in the United States, selling more than a million copies domestically,[1] while spawning two singles with top 10 hit "Show Stopper" and the ballad "Ride for You." Danity Kane&#039;s second studio album, Welcome to the Dollhouse, was released on March 18, 2008 following the release of the lead single "Damaged".[2]
